Package: duckbotos-browseros
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 curl,
 desktop-file-utils,
 xdg-utils
Description: DuckBotOS BrowserOS — default agentic web browser
 Installs BrowserOS as the default agentic web browser for DuckBotOS.
 BrowserOS is a Chromium fork with native AI agent support, providing
 53+ browser automation tools via MCP protocol.
 .
 CLI:      /usr/bin/browseros-cli
 Binary:   /opt/browseros/browseros
 MCP port: 9003 (localhost)
 .
 Set as default browser via update-alternatives:
   update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/x-www-browser browseros \
     /opt/browseros/browseros 200
 .
 Registered as x-www-browser for OS-wide use.
 Agent mode supports Claude Opus 4.5 and any OpenAI-compatible model.
 Chat mode supports any model including local LM Studio models.
 .
 NOTE: browseros-cli `status` is known to report "disconnected" even
 when working — use `browseros-cli health` and `browseros-cli pages`
 to verify real state.
